From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: James Turton <james.turton@gmx.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drm/sun4i: tcon_top: register reset/clocks in probe

TCON TOP registers its clock gates (including the DSI "mod" clock used by
the A100/D1/T113 MIPI-DSI controller) in its component bind callback. The
sun6i-mipi-dsi controller, however, fetches that "mod" clock in its own
platform probe, which runs before the sun4i-drm component master binds the
pipeline. The result is a deadlock specific to the D1/T113 DSI path:

  - DSI probe can't get the mod clock -> -EPROBE_DEFER, so it never calls
    component_add();
  - the component master therefore never has all its components and never
    binds;
  - so TCON TOP bind never runs and never registers the mod clock.

Boot logs show this as endless:
  sun6i-mipi-dsi 5450000.dsi: Couldn't get the DSI mod clock
  platform 5450000.dsi: deferred probe pending

Break the cycle by running the TCON TOP clock setup at probe time (reusing
the existing bind body) and turning the component bind into a stub, so the
clocks exist before any consumer probes. This mirrors the long-standing
out-of-tree fix from the Allwinner R40/D1 DSI work.

Signed-off-by: James Turton <james.turton@gmx.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/sun4i/sun8i_tcon_top.c | 27 ++++++++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 25 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/sun4i/sun8i_tcon_top.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/sun4i/sun8i_tcon_top.c
index 1111111111111..2222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/sun4i/sun8i_tcon_top.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/sun4i/sun8i_tcon_top.c
@@ -249,15 +249,35 @@ static void sun8i_tcon_top_unbind(struct device *dev, struct device *master,
 	clk_disable_unprepare(tcon_top->bus);
 	reset_control_assert(tcon_top->rst);
 }

+static int sun8i_tcon_top_dummy_bind(struct device *dev, struct device *master,
+				     void *data)
+{
+	return 0;
+}
+
 static const struct component_ops sun8i_tcon_top_ops = {
-	.bind	= sun8i_tcon_top_bind,
+	.bind	= sun8i_tcon_top_dummy_bind,
 	.unbind	= sun8i_tcon_top_unbind,
 };

 static int sun8i_tcon_top_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 {
-	return component_add(&pdev->dev, &sun8i_tcon_top_ops);
+	int ret;
+
+	/*
+	 * Register the TCON TOP reset, bus clock and clock gates (including
+	 * the DSI "mod" clock) at probe rather than at DRM component bind.
+	 * The MIPI-DSI controller fetches that clock during its own probe,
+	 * which runs before the sun4i-drm component master binds the
+	 * pipeline; registering it at bind deadlocks DSI probe.  Reuse the
+	 * existing bind body directly here.
+	 */
+	ret = sun8i_tcon_top_bind(&pdev->dev, NULL, NULL);
+	if (ret)
+		return ret;
+
+	return component_add(&pdev->dev, &sun8i_tcon_top_ops);
 }

 static void sun8i_tcon_top_remove(struct platform_device *pdev)
--
